<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!-- V8 JIT — required by Electron's Chromium runtime -->
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>

  <!-- Anthropic API + Minecraft TCP connect -->
  <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
  <true/>

  <!-- LAN multicast watcher (UDP receive bound to 0.0.0.0:4445) -->
  <key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
  <true/>

  <!-- Microphone (voice calls, 260707). Under the hardened runtime, macOS
       refuses getUserMedia audio capture without this entitlement even when the
       user has granted the TCC permission — the packaged/notarized app then
       silently fails to capture (works only in `npm run dev`, a different TCC
       identity). Pairs with NSMicrophoneUsageDescription in
       electron-builder.yml `mac.extendInfo` (the TCC prompt string). -->
  <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
  <true/>

  <!-- REMOVED 2026-06-21: com.apple.developer.networking.multicast.
       This is a RESTRICTED ("com.apple.developer.*") entitlement. macOS AMFI
       only honors it when the .app carries a matching embedded provisioning
       profile, and we ship Developer ID + notarized with NO profile embedded.
       Result: AMFI refused to spawn the signed/notarized app at launch —
         amfid: "Restricted entitlements not validated, bailing out.
                 Error -413 No matching profile found"
         launchd: INIT code 163 -> RBSRequestError "Launchd job spawn failed"
       which Finder surfaces as "The application Sei Launcher can't be opened."
       for EVERY user of v0.3.0. codesign verify, spctl and notarization all
       still passed because none of them check the entitlement/profile
       relationship that AMFI enforces at exec time.

       The multicast entitlement is an iOS/iPadOS/tvOS construct; on macOS the
       open-to-LAN beacon (224.0.2.60:4445) is gated by the Local Network
       privacy permission — NSLocalNetworkUsageDescription in electron-builder.yml
       `mac.extendInfo` (already present) plus network.server above — not by this
       entitlement. Removing it unbreaks launch with no expected macOS regression.

       If LAN detection ever genuinely needs this entitlement on macOS, do NOT
       just re-add the key — that re-bricks the app. Instead:
         1. Enable the Multicast Networking capability for App ID com.sei.app in
            the Apple Developer portal (an Apple-gated request).
         2. Generate a Developer ID provisioning profile that includes it.
         3. Set `mac.provisioningProfile: build/embedded.provisionprofile` in
            electron-builder.yml so it is embedded + sealed at sign time. -->

</dict>
</plist>
